Represents the GML MeasureType as defined in GML specification. This class stores a numeric Value measurement along with a mandatory UnitOfMeasure identifier.

Remarks

In the underlying schema (/2005/gml/basicTypes.xsd), MeasureType is an extension of double that requires a UnitOfMeasure (uom) attribute. By inheriting from ObservableDbEntity, any changes to UnitOfMeasure or Value trigger property change notifications, aiding in data binding and persistence.

The UnitOfMeasure property is recommended to follow the Unified Code for Units of Measure (UCUM), ensuring a standardized format (e.g., “kg”, “m/s”) that avoids restricted characters (:, ' ', \n, \r, \t). The Value property holds the numerical quantity, in line with the GML double base type.

Properties

UnitOfMeasure

Gets/Sets a character string of length at least one, and restricted such that it must not contain any of the following characters:

  • : (colon)
  • ' ' (space)
  • \n (newline)
  • \r (carriage return)
  • \t (tab)
This allows values corresponding to familiar abbreviations, such as 'kg', 'm/s', etc. 
[JsonProperty("uom")]
public string UnitOfMeasure { get; set; }

Property Value

string

Remarks

It is recommended that the symbol be an identifier for a unit of measure as specified in the

'Unified Code of Units of Measure' (UCUM).
This provides a set of symbols and a grammar for constructing identifiers for units of measure that are unique, and may be easily entered with a keyboard supporting the limited character set known as 7-bit ASCII.
ISO 2955 formerly provided a specification with this scope, but was withdrawn in 2001. UCUM largely follows ISO 2955 with modifications to remove ambiguities and other problems.
